Example 2:
Itinerary: A Relaxing Getaway to Sedona, Arizona with Friends

Day 1: Arrival and Settling In
- Arrive in Phoenix and rent a car for the drive up to Sedona.
- Check into your lodging for the weekend - choose from a cozy bed & breakfast or a luxurious resort.
- Take a stroll through downtown Sedona to explore the local shops and galleries.
- Enjoy dinner at one of the many excellent restaurants in town.

Day 2: Exploring Nature
- Start your day with an early morning hike up Cathedral Rock, one of Sedona's most iconic formations.
- After working up an appetite, head back into town for brunch at one of the numerous cafes offering stunning views of the red rocks.
- Spend the afternoon exploring more natural wonders like Bell Rock or Devil's Bridge Trail.

Day 3: Wellness Activities
- Begin your day with yoga classes offered by various studios throughout Sedona.
- Treat yourself to some pampering at one of Sedona's world-class spas known for their rejuvenating treatments inspired by Native American healing traditions.
- In the evening, attend a sound healing session or meditation workshop designed to help you relax and connect with nature.

Day 4: Departure
Before heading back home:
    - Savor breakfast at your favorite spot or indulge in gourmet brunch options unique only here;
    - Make last-minute stops at any must-do attractions you may have missed such as Montezuma Castle National Monument;
    - Head towards Phoenix Sky Harbor International Airport for departure. 

